<tr>
<td valign=3D"top" style=3D"border:none; border-bottom:solid #CCCCCC 1.0pt;=
 padding:0cm 15.0pt 0cm 15.0pt">
<p style=3D"line-height:10.5pt"><strong><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt; fon=
t-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif; color:black">Organize a Working Gr=
oup/Conference-within-a-Conference</span></strong><span style=3D"font-size:=
8.5pt; font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif; color:black"><br>
Individuals holding a Ph.D. may submit a proposal to convene a conference-w=
ithin-a-conference, or multiple organized sessions related to a single them=
e, topic, or area of study. Proposals are reviewed on a case-by-case basis.=
 The convenor(s) are responsible
 for recruiting participants, organizing them into sessions, and facilitati=
ng communication and cooperation within the group. MPSA staff will assign m=
eeting space, provide for the logistical needs of the group, maintain a ros=
ter of participants, help to promote
 the event, and work with the convenor(s) to accommodate scheduling request=
s. This is an excellent opportunity for cohorts to gather around specific a=
reas of study that may not be well-represented in the normal conference sec=
tions, or to develop specific projects
 like an edited volume. If you are interested in organizing a&nbsp;<a href=
=3D"https://go.mpsanet.org/e/875141/conference-working-groups-/2d4myj7/1267=
426734/h/TqDMeyvKMmyUN1VGgu0SGtFO77-HAVgzVq6Y9viN8iI"><span style=3D"color:=
#0000EE">Working Group or Conference-within-a-Conference</span></a>,
 contact MPSA Professional Development Manager, <a href=3D"mailto:hoss@mpsa=
net.org">
<span style=3D"color:#0000EE">Lewis Hoss, Ph.D</span></a>.<br>
<br>
</span><b><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt; font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,s=
ans-serif; color:black">Offer to Serve as a Chair or Discussant</span></b><=
span style=3D"font-size:8.5pt; font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif; =
color:black"><br>
Please consider volunteering your expertise to demonstrate your support of =
your colleagues in the discipline. Professional-level members and submitter=
s may volunteer to be a discussant or chair via the MPSA proposal system. S=
econd-year graduate students may
 volunteer to serve as a discussant on undergraduate sessions (poster sessi=
ons are for in-person participation only, no virtual option is available). =
You must be&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://go.mpsanet.org/e/875141/mpsacommunity-s=
-/2d4myht/1267426734/h/TqDMeyvKMmyUN1VGgu0SGtFO77-HAVgzVq6Y9viN8iI"><span s=
tyle=3D"color:#0000EE">logged
 in</span></a>&nbsp;with your MPSA username and password to volunteer.&nbsp=
;<i>All users must complete their profile before volunteering for a chair o=
r discussant role. You will be prompted to complete your account profile if=
 you have not done so already.</i>&nbsp;After logging
 in, click =93Volunteer to be a Chair or Discussant for a Section=94 in the=
 proposal system. Learn more about conference participation roles&nbsp;<a h=
ref=3D"https://go.mpsanet.org/e/875141/formats-and-role-descriptions-/2d4my=
kb/1267426734/h/TqDMeyvKMmyUN1VGgu0SGtFO77-HAVgzVq6Y9viN8iI"><span style=3D=
"color:#0000EE">here</span></a>.<br>
<br>
</span><strong><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt; font-family:&quot;Verdana&qu=
ot;,sans-serif; color:black">Schedule a Meeting or Reception at the Confere=
nce</span></strong><span style=3D"font-size:8.5pt; font-family:&quot;Verdan=
a&quot;,sans-serif; color:black"><br>
MPSA intends to hold some networking sessions,&nbsp;meetings&nbsp;and recep=
tions. Attendees are also invited to propose meetings,&nbsp;receptions&nbsp=
;and networking events for the conference.&nbsp;If your group needs to arra=
nge for a meeting, reception, or catered meal in conjunction
 with the 2026 MPSA Annual Conference, complimentary meeting and reception =
space is available to our professional colleagues on a first-to-ask, first-=
to-receive basis.&nbsp;If your group needs to arrange for a function at the=
 conference, please email MPSA Conference
 Administrator, <a href=3D"mailto:vandeventer@mpsanet.org"><span style=3D"c=
olor:#0000EE">Bonnie Van Deventer</span></a>.<br>
<br>
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif">Question=
s?</span></strong><br>
Please contact MPSA staff at&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:mpsainfo@mpsanet.org"><=
span style=3D"color:#0000EE">mpsainfo@mpsanet.org</span></a>.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
